<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-01-1136 </DOCNO><TEXT>Distortion of the cross section of a tokamak has been suggested as a meansof improving Ohmic heating and raising {beta} We have investigated theeffects of such distortion on the collisionless, electrostatic trapped-particlemode and find that under certain conditions a maximum-J configurationcan be approached. Results will be presented for finite elliptic andtriangular distortions, indicating significant stabilization. 6 refs.,4 figs.</TEXT></DOC>